obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9694)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9694&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Notaries Act, 1952.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1`
  line `* * *.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and theSchedule (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `2. 14th February, 1956: vide notification No. S.R.O. 317, dated 10th February, 1956, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `s. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9695)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9695&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) "instrument" includes every document by which any right or liability is, or purports to be,`
  line `created, transferred, modified, limited, extended, suspended, extinguished or recorded;`
  line
  line `^2[(c) "legal" practitioner means an advocate entered in any roll under the provisions of the`
  line `Advocates Act, 1961 (25 of 1961);]`
  line
  line `(d) "notary" means a person appointed as such under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that for a period of two years from the commencement of this Act it shall include also a`
  line `person who, before such commencement was appointed a notary public ^3`
  line `[under] the Negotiable`
  line `Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881),`
  line `^4* * * and is, immediately before such commencement, in`
  line `practice in^5`
  line `[any part of India:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in relation to the State of Jammu and Kashmir* the said period of two years`
  line `shall be computed from the date on which this Act comes into force in that State.]`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Register" means a Register of Notaries maintained by the Government under section 4;`
  line
  line `^6[(g) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the administrator thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Clause (a) omitted by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1999, s. 2, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and the Schedule, for "either under" (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or by Master of Faculties in England" omitted by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid., for "any part of India" (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by the A.O. (No. 3), 1956, for clause (g).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9696)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to appoint notaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9696&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, for the whole or any part of India, and any`
  line `State Government, for the whole or any part of the State, may appoint as notaries any legal practitioners`
  line `or other persons who possess such qualifications as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9697)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title Registers.
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9697&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government and every State Government shall maintain, in such form`
  line `as may be prescribed, a Register of the notaries appointed by that Government and entitled to practice as`
  line `such under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such Register shall include the following particulars about the notary whose name is`
  line `entered therein, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) his full name, date of birth, residential and professional address;`
  line
  line `(b) the date on which his name is entered in the Register;`
  line
  line `(c) his qualifications; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other particulars which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9698)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Entry of names in the Register and issue or renewal of certificates of practice.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9698&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every`
  line `notary who intends to practise as such ^1`
  line `[may] on payment to the Government appointing him of the`
  line `prescribed fee, if any, be entitled—`
  line
  line `(a) to have his name entered in the Register maintained by that Government under section 4, and`
  line
  line `(b) to a certificate authorising him to practise for a period of ^2`
  line `[five years] from the date on which`
  line `which the certificate is issued to him.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(2) The Government appointing the notary, may, on receipt of an application and the prescribed fee,`
  line `fee, renew the certificates of practice of any notary for a period of five years at a time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1999, s. 3, for "shall" (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "three years" (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9699)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Annual publication of lists of notaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9699&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government and every State Government`
  line `shall, during the month of January each year, publish in the Official Gazette a list of notaries appointed by`
  line `that Government and in practice at the beginning of that year together with such details pertaining to them`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9700)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Seal of notaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9700&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Every notary shall have and use, as occasion may arise, a seal of such form and`
  line `design as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9701)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Functions of notaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9701&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) A notary may do all or any of the following acts by virtue of his`
  line `office, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) verify, authenticate, certify or attest the execution of any instrument;`
  line
  line `(b) present any promissory note, hundi or bill of exchange for acceptance or payment or demand`
  line `better security;`
  line
  line `(c) note or protest the dishonour by non-acceptance or non-payment of any promissory note,`
  line `hundi or bill of exchange or protest for better security or prepare acts of honour under the Negotiable`
  line `Instruments Act, 1881 (26 of 1881), or serve notice of such note or protest;`
  line
  line `(d) note and draw up ship's protest, boat's protest or protest relating to demurrage and other`
  line `commercial matters;`
  line
  line `(e) administer oath to, or take affidavit from, any person;`
  line
  line `(f) prepare bottomry and respondentia bonds, charter parties and other mercantile documents;`
  line
  line `(g) prepare, attest or authenticate any instrument intended to take effect in any country or place`
  line `outside India in such form and language as may conform to the law of the place where such deed is`
  line `intended to operate;`
  line
  line `(h) translate, and verify the translation of, any document from one language into another;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(ha) act as a Commissioner to record evidence in any civil or criminal trial if so directed by any`
  line `court or authority;`
  line
  line `(hb) act as an arbitrator, mediator or conciliator, if so required;]`
  line
  line `(i) any other act which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No act specified in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a notarial act except when it is done by a`
  line `notary under his signature and official seal.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9702)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Bar of practice without certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9702&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, no person shall`
  line `practise as a notary or do any notarial act under the official seal of a notary unless he holds a certificate of`
  line `practice in force issued to him under section 5:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall apply to the presentation of any promissory note, hundi`
  line `or bill of exchange for acceptance or payment by the clerk of a notary acting on behalf of such notary.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall, until the expiry of two years from the commencement`
  line `of this Act, apply to any such person as is referred to in the proviso to clause (d) of section 2.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[Provided that in relation to the State of Jammu and Kashmir* the said period of two years shall be`
  line `computed from the date on which this Act comes into force in that State.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 25 of 1968, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-8-1968).`
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9703)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Removal of names from Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1999, s. 5, for "or" (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9703&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Government appointing any notary may, by order,`
  line `remove from the Register maintained by it under section 4 the name of the notary if he—`
  line
  line `(a) makes a request to that effect; or`
  line
  line `(b) has not paid any prescribed fee required to be paid by him; or`
  line
  line `(c) is an undischarged insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(d) has been found, upon inquiry in the prescribed manner, to be guilty of such professional or`
  line `other misconduct as, in the opinion of the Government, renders his unfit to practise as a notary; ^1`
  line [or]
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(e) is convicted by any court for an offence involving moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(f) does not get his certificate of practice renewed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (9704)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Construction of references to notaries public in other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9704&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any reference to a notary public`
  line `in any other law shall be construed as a reference to a notary entitled to practice under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (9705)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Penalty for falsely representing to be a notary, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "three months" (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9705&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Any person who—`
  line
  line `(a) falsely represents that he is a notary without being appointed as such, or`
  line
  line `(b) practises as a notary or does any notarial act in contravention of section 9,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ^1`
  line `[one year], or with fine, or with`
  line both.
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (9706)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Cognizance of offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9706&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Court shall take cognizance of any offence committed by a`
  line `notary in the exercise or purported exercise of his functions under this Act save upon complaint in writing`
  line `made by an officer authorised by the Central Government or a State Government by general or special`
  line `order in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) No Magistrate other than a Presidency Magistrate or a Magistrate of the first class shall try an`
  line `offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (9707)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Reciprocal arrangements for recognition of notarial acts done by foreign notaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9707&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `If the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied that by the law or practice of any country or place outside India, the`
  line `notarial acts done by notaries within India are recognised for all or any limited purposes in that country or`
  line `place, the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that the notarial acts`
  line `lawfully done by notaries within such country or place shall be recognised within India for all purposes`
  line `or, as the case may be, for such limited purposes as may be specified in the notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (9708)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9708&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the qualifications of a notary, the form and manner in which applications for appointment as a`
  line `notary may be made and the disposal of such applications;`
  line
  line `(b) the certificates, testimonials or proofs as to character, integrity, ability and competence which`
  line `any person applying for appointment as a notary may be required to furnish;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(c) the fees payable for appointment as a notary and for the issue and renewal of a certificate of`
  line `practice, area of practice or enlargement of area of practice and exemption whether wholly or in part,`
  line `from such fees in specified classes of cases;]`
  line
  line `(d) the fees payable to a notary for doing any notarial act;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of Registers and the particulars to be entered therein;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and design of the seal of a notary;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which inquiries into allegations of professional or other misconduct of notaries`
  line `may be made;`
  line
  line `(h) the acts which a notary may do in addition to those specified in section 8 and the manner in`
  line `which a notary may perform his functions;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 36 of 1999, s. 7, for clause (c) (w.e.f. 17-12-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 20 of 1983, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-3-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (9709)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336&sectionId=9709&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00007_195253_1517807328336
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of Act 26 of 1881]. Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1957 (36 of 1957), s. 2`
  line `and Schedule I.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
